list.item:
Pregnancy, because there is no reason to use COCs during pregnancy[ see Warnings and Precautions (5.9)
                              and Use in Specific Populations (8.1)
                              ]

text.paragraph:
Administration of COCs to induce withdrawal bleeding should not be used as a test for pregnancy [
                           see Use in Specific Populations (8.1)
                           ].

list.item:
Vascular events[
                              see Warnings and Precautions (5.1)
                              ]

Liver disease[
                              see Warnings and Precautions (5.2)
                              ]

text.paragraph:
The safety and efficacy of Microgestin 24 Fe in women with a body mass index (BMI) > 35 kg/m2 has not been evaluated [see 
                           Clinical Studies (14)
                           ].
